# Based on Fefe's talk at 36c3:
# https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=31xA9p3pYE4

O++     # No explicit license yet, but ...
S++     # The source code is public and you can change it
I++     # I have done this multiple times before. I know what I'm doing (but do you know what I'm doing?)
C       # I'm the only user I know about.
E       # Well, mostly. And the remaining case is simple
M       # Several new features in last 6 months
V+      # Well, the updates aren't regular, but they shouldn't break anything
!PS     # Not complex enough to need a spec
D+      # Only the obvious dependencies

